"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824679","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-25","<p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: <a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</a>. Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: <a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a>.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123478","2018-01-25T15:48:25.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824679/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824679/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Treasury: Public Private Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, How many (a) PFI and (b) PF2 contracts were signed by his Department since 13 July 2016.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824680","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-22","<p>The Libraries Taskforce, which reports to the Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport and the Local Government Association, plays an important role in promoting good practice and leadership across the public libraries sector in England.</p><p>The Department encourages all councils, including Northamptonshire County Council, to make use of the information and guidance made available by the Taskforce. This includes toolkits published by the Taskforce on alternative delivery models and longer term evidence based sustainable planning, to support councils as they plan their future library provision to make sure that it is sustainable, and meets the needs of local residents.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-01-22T17:03:05.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824680/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824680/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-17","Public Libraries: Northamptonshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will take joint steps with the Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport and Northamptonshire County Council to facilitate active engagement between Northamptonshire County Council and the Government Libraries Task Force on developing a plan to keep open all Northamptonshire publicly-funded libraries.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","123481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824681","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-25","<p>Departments continually monitor the operational performance of contracts to ensure the best outcome for taxpayers.</p><p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive. Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: <a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a>.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123493","2018-01-25T15:50:01.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824681/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824681/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what criteria his Department has used to approve and monitor contracts to Carillion since 2010; and what due diligence his Department undertakes before awarding contracts to companies that have issued profit warnings.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824682","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-24","<p>The Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government publishes regular statistics on rough sleeping, statutory homelessness and homelessness prevention and relief. These are published at a local authority level. The latest statistics can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics</a>.</p><p>We are supporting 48 projects through our £20 million Rough Sleeping Grant, with £470,000 awarded to Cornwall for services to work in partnership and prevent people from sleeping rough through identifying those at risk as well as assisting people into emergency accommodation.</p><p>The Government remains committed to combating homelessness and rough sleeping. No one should ever have to sleep rough. That is why we are aiming to halve rough sleeping by 2022 and eliminate it altogether by 2027. To achieve this, we have set up a Rough Sleeping and Homelessness Reduction Taskforce that will focus on prevention and affordable housing.</p><p>We also supported the Homelessness Reduction Act which commences in April 2018. The Act significantly reforms England’s homelessness legislation, ensuring that more people get the help they need earlier to prevent them from becoming homeless in the first place.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-01-24T14:22:36.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824682/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824682/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824682/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-17","Homelessness: Cornwall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of homeless people in Cornwall; and what assessment he has made of the trend in the level of homelessness in that area in the past five years.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","123483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824683","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-25","<p>Treasury ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123471 ; 123472 ; 123499 ; 123501","2018-01-25T15:45:48.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824683/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824683/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824683/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, What discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the effect of the liquidation of Carillion plc on (a) jobs and (b) public finances.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824684","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-23","<p>VisitBritain and VisitEngland are responsible for promoting the UK as a tourist destination, which it does through a range of different initiatives and campaigns. One of the current projects in the £40m Discover England Fund is the South West Coast Path, which is promoting the path to the Dutch and German market. Cornwall is also featured in their new domestic campaign “Join the World”.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>At of the end of the last financial year, the Heritage Lottery Fund has funded 639 projects totalling £104.3m in Cornwall. These projects range from the St Austell Townscape Heritage, the Tate St Ives and the National Maritime Museum in Falmouth. In addition, our colleagues in the Department of Cities and Local Growth have awarded over £11m of Coastal Communities Funding to 12 projects in Cornwall.</p><p><strong><p><p><br></strong></p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis","123160","2018-01-23T15:43:26.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824684/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824684/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824684/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-17","Tourism: North Cornwall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what funding his Department has allocated for the promotion of tourism in north Cornwall.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","123485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824685","Department for Education","false","2018-01-25","<p>The department collects data on the weekly regional cost of childcare through our regular parent surveys. These can be found at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-childcare-and-early-years" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-childcare-and-early-years</a>.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-25T14:53:50.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824685/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824685/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824685/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average weekly cost was of a childcare place in Cornwall in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","123486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824686","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-25","<p>Prior to the provisional settlement, my Department held a technical consultation in September 2017 on the planned approach to the 2018-19 local government finance settlement. We received a total of 330 representations of which none were from Cornish business groups.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-01-25T18:05:12.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824686/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824686/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824686/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-17","Local Government Finance: Cornwall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many representations he has received from Cornish business groups prior to the announcement of the local government finance settlement.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","123487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824687","Department for Education","false","2018-01-25","<p>This is a matter for Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector, Amanda Spielman. I have asked her to write to you and a copy of her reply will be placed in the Libraries of both Houses.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-01-25T17:57:30.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824687/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824687/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824687/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Academies: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many schools that have been converted to academies have not been inspected by Ofsted within three years of opening.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824688","Department for Education","false","2018-01-25","<p>Two schools in Bethnal Green and Bow constituency have become academies since 2010. The Green Spring Academy Shoreditch opened in 2012 and the Old Ford Primary School opened in 2013.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-25T16:38:02.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824688/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824688/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824688/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Academies: Bethnal Green and Bow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many schools in Bethnal Green and Bow constituency have become an academy in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824689","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-25","<p>Our top priority is to keep public services running. We have carried out extensive scenario planning, and expect all vital public services to run as normal. Government will provide funding for public services to enable them to continue in the immediate future and to enable some of them to be run by new suppliers.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-01-25T14:46:57.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824689/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824689/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824689/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of the cost to the public purse of replacing Carillion contracts.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824690","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-24","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) is currently undertaking a programme of large scale technical change to enhance its services. As part of this work, the DVLA is reviewing the way refunds of vehicle excise duty are paid.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-01-24T15:00:05.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824690/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824690/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824690/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-17","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of changing the repayment system for Vehicle Excise Duty so that money is paid directly into bank accounts instead of by cheque.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","123491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824691","Department for Education","false","2018-01-25","<p>On 19 December 2017, we published ’30 hours free childcare: autumn term 2017’ which showed for the first time the number of children in a 30 hours place.</p><p> </p><p>This showed that, based on local authority returns to a voluntary survey, an estimated 202,800 children were in a 30 hours place. At a national level, this was 90% of the total number of codes generated. At a regional level this ranged from 85% in the South East to 97% in the North East.</p><p> </p><p>This is the first term of delivering a new national programme and it is encouraging that no region has under 85% of children with a 30 hours code in a 30 hours place. We cannot account for a parents’ preference and behaviour which could, of course, vary across the country depending on individual circumstances.</p><p> </p><p>Our new Early Years National Funding Formula includes an ‘Area Cost Adjustment’ to reflect the fact that the costs of delivering childcare vary between different local authority areas. We will monitor all 30 hours data over the first year of delivery to understand how the new policy is being delivered and identify any operational challenges.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-25T16:50:46.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824691/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824691/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824691/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment the Government has made of the regional disparities in funded childcare places in England.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824692","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-25","<p>Departments continually monitor the operational performance of contracts to ensure the best outcome for taxpayers.</p><p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive. Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at: <a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a>.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123482","2018-01-25T15:50:01.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824692/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824692/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824692/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, If he will place a copy of each risk assessment undertaken by his Department relating to Government contracts secured by Carillion since January 2015 in the Library.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824693","Department for Education","false","2018-01-25","<p>Ofsted is the non-ministerial government department responsible for the regulation of early education and childcare providers. They publish a regular series of statistics relating to early years providers, which can be viewed from this link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/ofsted/about/statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/ofsted/about/statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>This is a matter for Ofsted. I have asked, Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector, Amanda Spielman, to write to the hon. Member. A copy of her reply will be placed in the Libraries of both Houses.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-25T15:05:15.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824693/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824693/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824693/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many childcare providers in (a) Bethnal Green and Bow, (b) London and (c) England have fallen off the register in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824694","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-24","<p>Our priority is to keep public services running. We have extensive contingency plans and are working hard to minimise any disruption.</p><p> </p><p>We have worked closely across government with all affected departments and stakeholders to develop robust contingency plans that enable us to maintain the continuity and mitigate impacts to public services where possible.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-01-24T17:30:48.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824694/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824694/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824694/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Government Departments: Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent discussions he has had with other Government Departments on (a) drawing up contingency plans and (b) identifying alternative suppliers to provide the public services previously provided by Carillion.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824695","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-24","<p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</a></p><p> </p><p>Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","123461","2018-01-24T17:30:38.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824695/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824695/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824695/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to each contract that the Government currently has with Carillion and its subsidiary companies (a) when each such contract was awarded, (b) which Department or agency awarded the contract, (c) how much each contract is worth and (d) whether the contract is a joint venture.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824696","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-29","<p>I refer the Honourable Member to the answer I gave on 22 December 2017 to the Honourable Member for Tottenham (PQ119871).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>To date, HMRC have received 3,496 complaints from parents who have experienced technical issues with the childcare service.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC have paid £966,666 to parents in lieu of any Tax-Free Childcare payments and £38,949 in redress to parents which recompense parents for inconvenience and expenses such as telephone calls to the helpline.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123498 ; 123500","2018-01-29T10:36:33.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824696/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824696/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824696/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much compensation to date the Government has paid out as a result of problems with the new childcare website.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123497"
