"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824698","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-25","<p>Treasury ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123471 ; 123472 ; 123484 ; 123501","2018-01-25T15:45:48.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824698/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824698/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824698/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Carillion: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish the minutes of any meetings which were held between Carillion and (a) HM Revenue and Customs and (b) his Department on monitoring the performance of Carillion in the last three years.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824699","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-29","<p>I refer the Honourable Member to the answer I gave on 22 December 2017 to the Honourable Member for Tottenham (PQ119871).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>To date, HMRC have received 3,496 complaints from parents who have experienced technical issues with the childcare service.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC have paid £966,666 to parents in lieu of any Tax-Free Childcare payments and £38,949 in redress to parents which recompense parents for inconvenience and expenses such as telephone calls to the helpline.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123497 ; 123498","2018-01-29T10:36:33.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824699/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824699/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824699/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has been made of the number of parents receiving childcare vouchers who will not be eligible for tax-free childcare.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824700","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-25","<p>Treasury ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations are published on a quarterly basis and are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123471 ; 123472 ; 123484 ; 123499","2018-01-25T15:45:48.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824700/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824700/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824700/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Carillion: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, If he will publish the dates of any meetings which were held between Carillion and (a) HMRC and (b) his Department on monitoring the performance of Carillion in the past five years.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","123501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824701","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-25","<p>The UK proposed and secured a UN Security Council Presidential Statement on 6 November that urged the Governments of Burma and Bangladesh to ensure the voluntary, safe and dignified return to Burma of Rohingya refugees, and the full participation of the UN High Commissioner for Refugees in the repatriation process.</p><p>We have repeatedly used our bilateral representations to the Governments of Burma and Bangladesh to call on them to ensure the repatriation process meets these conditions. The British Ambassador to Burma most recently pressed for UNHCR involvement in the repatriation process in his meeting with the Minister for the Office of the State Counsellor on 11 January. The British High Commission in Dhaka regularly raises our concerns about premature returns with the government of Bangladesh.</p><p>We share UNHCR's concerns regarding the risk of premature or precipitous returns, and its assessment that conditions in Rakhine are not presently in place to enable safe and sustainable returns.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-01-25T16:32:07.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824701/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824701/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824701/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-17","Burma: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps are being taken to ensure that the repatriation of Rohingya people from Bangladesh is overseen by an independent UN monitor to help ensure the safety and security of those refugees.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824702","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-25","<p>The UK has been actively maintaining dialogue on Burma within the EU, including in discussions in the Asia-Oceania Working Party, the Political and Security Committee, and the Foreign Affairs Council. EU coordination can be seen through the retention of the EU arms embargo and the suspension of all military visits to the UK. The UK was instrumental in securing EU wide support for these measures.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-01-25T16:33:07.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824702/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824702/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824702/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-17","Burma: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions has he had with his counterparts in other EU countries on ensuring a joined-up response to the Rohingya crisis.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824703","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-25","<p>The UNHCR holds the expertise on refugee returns which is why the government has repeatedly called for their involvement in both Bangladesh and Burma. We have discussed this directly with the UNHCR, most recently on 12 January in a meeting between FCO-DFID Minister Alastair Burt and the High Commissioner for Refugees, Filippo Grandi. We have also raised it in the UN Security Council, through the Presidential Statement on 6 November and in our intervention during the 12 December Council session. The UK has always been clear that refugee returns must be safe, voluntary and dignified. In our view guaranteed safety for the Rohingya once they are in northern Rakhine requires independent international oversight of the returns process.</p><p> </p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-01-25T16:34:32.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824703/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824703/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824703/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-17","Burma: Rohingya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the UN on the need for UN security for the protection of the repatriated Rohingya people.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","123504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824704","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-01-24","<p>The appointment of the Tree Champion is one of the priorities of the recently published 25 Year Environment Plan. The Tree Champion role will promote the benefits that trees deliver, support the tree planting manifesto commitments and co-ordinate a cross government approach to encourage a step change in tree planting.</p><p> </p><p>Further details will be agreed in due course, including the date of appointment.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-01-24T13:58:13.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824704/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824704/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824704/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-17","Forestry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he plans to appoint the national tree champion.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","123505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824705","Department for Education","false","2018-01-22","<p>Since 18 September 2017, real-time data on Sure Start children’s centres and children’s centre linked sites has been supplied by local authorities via the department’s Get Information about Schools (GIAS) database portal at: <a href="https://www.get-information-schools.service.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://www.get-information-schools.service.gov.uk/</a>.</p><p>Based on the information supplied by local authorities[1], the attached spreadsheet provides details of the location of children’s centres that have closed since 2010.</p><p>Councils are reconfiguring services to deliver them more efficiently. If a council decides to close a children’s centre, statutory guidance is clear that they should demonstrate that local children and families would not be adversely affected and local areas continue to have sufficient children’s centres to meet their needs.</p><p> </p><p>[1] The list of children’s centres closed since 2010 is based on information supplied by local authorities as at 18 August 2018 (10:30am).</p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-22T17:51:40.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824705/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824705/answer","123506 - attachment - 180118.xlsx","123506 - attachment - 180118.xlsx","123506 Table","123506 Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824705/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Children's Centres: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will publish the (a) location and (b) name of Sure Start centres that have closed since 2010.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","123506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824706","Department for Education","false","2018-01-22","<p>Funding for children's services (including children's centres) gives local authorities the freedom to decide how best to target resources and respond flexibly to meet local need. Local authorities must meet their statutory duties on children’s centres from funding that currently forms part of the Department for Communities and Local Government Business Rates Retention Scheme.</p><p> </p><p>Since April 2010, local authorities have reported expenditure on children’s centres (combined with early years) through annual Section 251 returns. This information is published at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-local-authority-school-finance-data#local-authority-and-school-finance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-local-authority-school-finance-data#local-authority-and-school-finance</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/section-251-materials" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/section-251-materials</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Other government funding, including that for public health, adult skills training and troubled families may also be used locally to support services delivered wholly, or in part, through children’s centres.</p><p> </p><p>The department does not hold data on the number of families that access health and support services through children’s centres centrally. This data is held at a local area level.</p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-22T17:57:02.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824706/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824706/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824706/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Sure Start Programme: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much funding from the public purse has been allocated to the Sure Start programme in each local authority; and how many families accessed health and support from the Sure Start programme within each local authority in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","123507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824707","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-25","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has not published any guidance on the treatment of gray zone lymphoma nor is it in the topic selection process for technology appraisals and highly specialised technologies guidance.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-01-25T14:06:07.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824707/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824707/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824707/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-17","Gray Zone Lymphoma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what guidance  NICE has issued on gray zone lymphoma.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","123508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824708","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-25","<p>Clinical commissioning groups take decisions on how their National Health Service budgets are spent on commissioning services to meet the needs of local populations, including those for gray zone lymphoma.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-01-25T14:04:35.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824708/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824708/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824708/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-17","Gray Zone Lymphoma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what public funds are available to treat patients suffering from gray zone lymphoma.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","123509"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824709","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-22","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith","123520","2018-01-22T14:03:34.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824709/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824709/answer","PQ123510 & PQ123520.pdf","PQ123510 & PQ123520.pdf","UKSA Response ","UKSA Response ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824709/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Lung Cancer: Halton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people have been diagnosed with lung cancer in Halton constituency in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","123510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824710","Department for Education","false","2018-01-24","<p>The Department for Education does not hold information on complaints made in relation to reconfirmation of eligibility for 30 hours free childcare. Her Majesty’s Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will release further information on complaints they have received in due course.</p><p> </p><p>The vast majority of parents are using the digital childcare service without issue. As shown in our management information release, 30 hours free childcare eligibility codes issued and validated: January 2018, more than 325,000 eligibility codes have been issued for the spring term. The department continues to work closely with HMRC to support parents through the application process for 30 hours free childcare.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-24T19:04:55.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824710/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824710/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many formal complaints have been made to HMRC on problems with reconfirming eligibility codes for 30 hours of free funded childcare for three and four-year-old children since April 2017; and whether his Department has made an assessment of HMRC’s capacity to efficiently process applications for 30 hours of free childcare.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","123511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824711","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-23","<p>The latest available information on Employment and Support Allowance Work Capability Assessments appeal outcomes can be found in tables 3 and 17 of the ESA Outcomes of Work Capability Assessments quarterly statistics published here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-outcomes-of-work-capability-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-outcomes-of-work-capability-assessment</a></p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-01-23T11:39:58.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824711/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824711/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824711/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-17","Employment and Support Allowance: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of claimants who did not qualify for Employment Support Allowance made successful appeals in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","123512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824712","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-24","<p>As these are matters between tenants and landlords and not directly related to the provision of benefits, the Department can collect data on from its systems.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-01-24T10:47:08.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824712/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824712/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-17","Universal Credit: Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate she has made of the number of claimants of universal credit in private and housing association accommodation who have received a (a) threat of eviction or (b) court summons since the introduction that benefit.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","123513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824713","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-25","<p>This information is not available.</p><p> </p><p>If a Local Authority considers that a claimant requires further financial assistance towards their housing costs (including rent in advance, deposits and supporting tenants through the transition to welfare reforms), they can award a Discretionary Housing Payment, in addition to welfare benefits.</p><p> </p><p>This may enable Housing Benefit or Universal Credit claimants to stay in their properties, but non-payment of rent isn’t the only reason why evictions take place in. Tenants are also be evicted because of anti-social behaviour or criminal activities.</p><p> </p><p>Social landlords in particular design their policies to ensure that any evictions are carried out only after other options have been exhausted, tenants have failed to engage with their landlord or tenancy management remedies have proved ineffective.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-01-25T10:30:56.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824713/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824713/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824713/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-17","Employment and Support Allowance: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate she has made of the number of people who were successful in appeals for Employment Support Allowance were (a) evicted or (b) threatened with eviction in the period between the original assessment and the appeal decision.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","123514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824714","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-22","<p>The Department’s data on payment timeliness is not broken down by area or region.</p><p> </p><p>However, data published on 2 October 2017 shows that, nationally, 81% of new full service claims received their first payment in full and on time. Across the whole of Universal Credit, 92% of all households received their full payment on time. The published data can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-payment-timeliness-january-to-june-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-payment-timeliness-january-to-june-2017</a>.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-01-22T16:39:32.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824714/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824714/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-17","Universal Credit: Halton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have had payment of universal credit delayed by (a) one week, (b) two weeks, (c) three weeks or (d) four weeks or more in Halton constituency during the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","123515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824715","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-25","<p>The number of appeals allowed in the First-tier Tribunal (Immigration and Asylum Chamber) over the last three years is: 2014/2015 – 26,394; 2015/2016 – 20,539 and 2016/2017 – 23,275.</p><p> </p><p>Timescales from receipt to disposal of an appeal are not routinely broken down by outcome and could not be provided in the time available.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-01-25T18:38:42.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824715/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824715/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-17","Immigration: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many immigration appeals at tribunal have been successful; and how many of those appeals were within six months, for each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","123516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824716","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-22","<p>The information available on the number of people and households on Universal Credit by parliamentary constituency, including a split by whether the household has received a payment or a nil award, can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a>. Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started.html</a></p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-01-22T16:40:02.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824716/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824716/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-17","Universal Credit: Halton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people are in receipt of universal credit in Halton constituency.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","123517"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824717","Department for Education","false","2018-01-22","<p>All Carillion apprentices are employed by Carillion Construction. The department is working with the Construction Industry Training Board (CITB) to find alternative employers for those apprentices to complete their apprenticeships. No apprentices have had their employment contract with Carillion Construction terminated by the Insolvency Service.</p><p> </p><p>Learners attending Carillion training centres, who are funded through a study programme will continue to receive training and this will be delivered by CITB or their partner colleges.</p><p> </p><p>The CITB are utilising their existing employer contacts in the sector and the grant incentives they have available. To find and secure alternative employers for the apprentices to complete their frameworks or standards. Additionally, they are making direct contact with companies in Carillion’s supply chain. CITB have reported that numerous employers have responded positively with offers of support.</p><p> </p><p>The CITB have contacted all affected learners to begin the transfer process, with a focus on minimising disruption to the learner and their learner journey. They have established a dedicated helpline to support those affected and have scheduled a series of workshops for learners, which will take place in the regions of the 11 Carillion Training Centres. These workshops will provide advice on next steps and offer 1 to 1 support as required. The timings and locations of these events have been communicated to the learners through telephone calls, email and a comprehensive social media campaign. Carillion are also actively encouraging their learners to attend these regional events.</p><p> </p><p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) are meeting with CITB daily to monitor progress and resolve issues.</p><p> </p><p>The ESFA funds training providers for their delivery of apprenticeships in arrears, so payments made have been calculated based on the activity recorded by Carillion and returned to the ESFA in monthly Individual learner records.</p><p>Normal ESFA audit requirements will continue to apply and there must be evidence of participation in learning for funds to be earned. We will reconcile payments when the liquidator makes a final claim for training delivered by Carillion.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","123281 ; 123519","2018-01-22T17:52:57.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824717/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824717/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps he is taking to find placements for the apprentices who have been transferred from Carillion Training Services to the Construction Industry Training Board.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","123518"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824718","Department for Education","false","2018-01-22","<p>All Carillion apprentices are employed by Carillion Construction. The department is working with the Construction Industry Training Board (CITB) to find alternative employers for those apprentices to complete their apprenticeships. No apprentices have had their employment contract with Carillion Construction terminated by the Insolvency Service.</p><p> </p><p>Learners attending Carillion training centres, who are funded through a study programme will continue to receive training and this will be delivered by CITB or their partner colleges.</p><p> </p><p>The CITB are utilising their existing employer contacts in the sector and the grant incentives they have available. To find and secure alternative employers for the apprentices to complete their frameworks or standards. Additionally, they are making direct contact with companies in Carillion’s supply chain. CITB have reported that numerous employers have responded positively with offers of support.</p><p> </p><p>The CITB have contacted all affected learners to begin the transfer process, with a focus on minimising disruption to the learner and their learner journey. They have established a dedicated helpline to support those affected and have scheduled a series of workshops for learners, which will take place in the regions of the 11 Carillion Training Centres. These workshops will provide advice on next steps and offer 1 to 1 support as required. The timings and locations of these events have been communicated to the learners through telephone calls, email and a comprehensive social media campaign. Carillion are also actively encouraging their learners to attend these regional events.</p><p> </p><p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) are meeting with CITB daily to monitor progress and resolve issues.</p><p> </p><p>The ESFA funds training providers for their delivery of apprenticeships in arrears, so payments made have been calculated based on the activity recorded by Carillion and returned to the ESFA in monthly Individual learner records.</p><p>Normal ESFA audit requirements will continue to apply and there must be evidence of participation in learning for funds to be earned. We will reconcile payments when the liquidator makes a final claim for training delivered by Carillion.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","123281 ; 123518","2018-01-22T17:52:57.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824718/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824718/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps he is taking to protect public funds allocated to Carillion Training Services for training apprentices from being used for other purposes.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","123519"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824719","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-22","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith","123510","2018-01-22T14:03:34.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824719/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824719/answer","PQ123510 & PQ123520.pdf","PQ123510 & PQ123520.pdf","UKSA Response ","UKSA Response ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824719/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Prostate Cancer: Halton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many men in Halton constituency have been diagnosed with prostate cancer in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","123520"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824720","Department for Education","false","2018-01-22","<p>Local authorities, academy trusts and colleges are responsible for their contracts. The department is, however, working with local authorities and academy trusts to make sure they have robust contingency plans in place and that these have been actioned where required. Information available to the department indicates that the number of local authority and academy trust schools covered by catering, facilities management or other service contracts with Carillion is relatively low.</p><p>The government’s priority is to ensure schools can continue to operate as usual. Government is supporting the official receiver, so that services to schools, including the provision of school meals, can continue to be delivered.</p><p>We are continuing to monitor the situation and will work with schools and providers to help minimise any disruption for pupils.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-22T17:42:16.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824720/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824720/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824720/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what information his Department holds on contracts held with Carillion Group for the provision of school meals.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","123521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824721","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-22","<p>Detailed information on contracts within local authorities is not held centrally.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-01-22T16:24:48.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824721/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824721/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824721/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what information his Department holds on contracts between Carillion and (a) schools, (b) colleges, (c) universities, (d) nurseries and (e) other public education institutions.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","123522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824722","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-23","<p>In 2015, households in England off the gas grid were more likely to be in fuel poverty (15.2%) compared to those on the gas grid (10.4%) and the depth of their fuel poverty was more severe - households off the gas grid had an average fuel poverty gap of £607 compared to £296 for those that were on the gas grid.</p><p> </p><p>Households off the gas grid made up 18.5 per cent of the total number of fuel poor households, whereas, households on the gas grid made up 81.5 per cent.</p><p> </p><p>The data in the attached document is from Table 10 of our fuel poverty detailed tables which can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-detailed-tables-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-detailed-tables-2017</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-01-23T13:48:38.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824722/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824722/answer","Attachment to 123523.pdf","Attachment to 123523.pdf","Table 10","Table 10","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824722/answer","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824722/answer/previousversion/36012","Biography information for Claire Perry","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-17","Fuel Poverty: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the level of fuel poverty of households which are off the gas grid.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","123523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824723","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-24","<p>In 2015, households in England in Rural areas were more likely to be in fuel poverty (13.6%) compared to both households in Semi-Rural areas (10.5%) and households in Urban areas (10.8%).</p><p> </p><p>Rural households made up 10.5 per cent of the total number of fuel poor households, whereas Semi-Rural households made up 9.1 per cent of fuel poor households, and Urban households made up 80.5 per cent of fuel poor households.</p><p> </p><p>The data attached is from Table 5 of our fuel poverty detailed tables which can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-detailed-tables-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fuel-poverty-detailed-tables-2017</a></p><p>Rurality definitions come from the Office for National Statistics (ONS): ‘Rural’ – Villages, hamlets and isolated dwellings; ‘Semi-Rural’ – Towns and fringe; ‘Urban’ – Urban.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-01-24T16:13:35.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824723/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824723/answer","Attachment to 123524.pdf","Attachment to 123524.pdf","Table 5","Table 5","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824723/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-17","Fuel Poverty: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the levels of fuel poverty in rural communities.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","123524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824724","Department for Education","false","2018-01-22","<p>The department has been working closely with Her Majesty’s Revenue &amp; Customs during the past 13 months to raise awareness of the apprenticeship levy amongst all employers who are required to pay it.</p><p>Communications include direct mail, phone calls and the use of trade publications and key business intermediaries that cover over one million employer members. National Apprenticeship Service account managers are also working directly with the largest 1,100 levy-paying employers who account for approximately 70 per cent of the levy, to make sure they are aware of any payments due. A further 4,500 levy-paying employers are being supported through a dedicated telephone account management service.</p><p>We are monitoring registrations on the apprenticeship service and continue to target communications at groups that have yet to register.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-01-22T17:20:56.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824724/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824724/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824724/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-17","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment his Department has made of the awareness of the apprenticeship levy among employers who are required to pay it.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","123525"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824725","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-22","<p>PwC are not the Official Receivers. Information on the role of PwC within Carillion is held by the Insolvency Service who are the contracting authority for this work.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","123527","2018-01-22T16:30:03.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824725/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824725/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824725/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of the appointment of PwC as official receivers for Carillion.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824726","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-22","<p>PwC are not the Official Receivers. Information on the role of PwC within Carillion is held by the Insolvency Service who are the contracting authority for this work.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","123526","2018-01-22T16:30:03.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824726/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824726/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824726/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many PwC employees are currently working on the management of Carillion; and how long he expects PwC to remain involved with the management of Carillion.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824727","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-29","<p>We are doing everything we can to support Carillion’s subcontractors and suppliers impacted by this collapse, but taxpayers should not, and will not, bail out a private sector company for private sector losses or allow rewards for failure.</p><p>We have also set up a taskforce to advise on the impact on small businesses and employees affected by Carillion insolvency. It will act as a means for government to communicate to those affected by Carillion’s liquidation, assess wider economic impacts and consider how to ensure that employees are provided with the right support to maximise swift re-employment.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-29T10:12:47.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824727/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824727/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824727/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether his Department undertook any economic feasibility studies on the effects that the liquidation of Carillion would have on small businesses in their supply chain before deciding not to provide financial assistance to Carillion.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824728","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-25","<p>HM Inspectorate of Prisons (HMIP) undertook an inspection of HMP Liverpool on 4-15 September 2017. The report of that inspection and the corresponding action plan were published on Friday 19 January. The plan sets out our actions to respond to issues which the inspectorate has raised.</p><p> </p><p>The action plan along with the HMIP inspection report for HMP Liverpool can be found on prison finder at <a href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/contacts/prison-finder/liverpool" target="_blank">http://www.justice.gov.uk/contacts/prison-finder/liverpool</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-01-25T15:50:32.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824728/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824728/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824728/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-17","Liverpool Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to publish his Department's action plan for HMP Liverpool.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","123529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824729","Department for International Development","false","2018-01-24","<p>On 9 January 2018 the Secretary of State for International Development met with the OECD’s Development Assistance Committee (DAC) Chair, for an introductory meeting. Since the October 2017 DAC High Level Meeting her officials have continued discussions on ODA reform, Department for International Development officials, including the UK’s representative for development to the OECD, speak regularly with their counterparts from other DAC Member States and the DAC Secretariat.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-01-24T17:18:20.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824729/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824729/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824729/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-17","International Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what discussions her Department has had with her Development Assistance Committee counterparts on changing international aid rules since her appointment as Secretary of State.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","123530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824730","Attorney General","true","2018-02-01","<p>The Government Legal Department (GLD)<ins class="ministerial"> holds contracts with eight Government strategic suppliers</ins> and Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) hold six contracts <del class="ministerial">each</del> with Government strategic suppliers.</p><p>The Serious Fraud Office (SFO) holds three contracts with Government strategic suppliers.</p><p>HMCPSI holds two contracts with Government strategic suppliers; and the Attorney General’s Office (AGO) holds <del class="ministerial">one</del> contract<ins class="ministerial">s with three suppliers</ins>.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2018-02-01T17:39:32.377Z","2018-03-23T14:34:08.293Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824730/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824730/answer","South Swindon","Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824730/answer/previousversion/38874","Biography information for Robert Buckland","88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-01-17","Attorney General: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many contracts his Department holds with government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824731","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-24","<p>From the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy’s, centrally held contract register (which shows contracts with a whole-life value in excess of £100k only) we have identified the following contracts strategic suppliers:-</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Supplier</p></td><td><p>Number of contracts</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Capita</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>CGI</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>IBM (UK) Limited</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Serco</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>12</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-01-24T16:48:34.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824731/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824731/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-17","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many contracts his Department holds with government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824732","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-08","<p>Since January 2011, details of central government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</a></p><p> </p><p>Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a></p><p> </p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-08T16:17:51.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824732/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824732/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824732/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-17","Cabinet Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many contracts his Department holds with government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123533"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824734","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-23","<p>The Crown Representatives and Strategic Suppliers list is as shown at the website below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/strategic-suppliers" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/strategic-suppliers</a></p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-01-23T17:17:33.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824734/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824734/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824734/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-17","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many contracts his Department holds with Government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824735","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-25","<p>The Ministry of Defence currently holds 1,029 contracts with the Government's strategic suppliers.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-01-25T16:55:45.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824735/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824735/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824735/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-17","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many contracts his Department holds with Government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824736","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-22","<p>The Industrial Strategy sets out a long term approach and its implementation will continue over the course of the parliament. The strategy covers a wide range of government commitments, including:</p><ul><li>committing to raising investment in R&amp;D to 2.4 per cent of GDP by 2027</li><li>announcing £725m in new Industrial Strategy Challenge Fund programmes to drive innovation</li><li>creating a £1.7bn Transforming Cities Fund for projects that drive productivity by improving connections within city regions</li><li>creating a new National Retraining Scheme that supports people to re-skill, beginning with a £64m investment for digital and construction training</li><li>increasing the National Productivity Investment Fund to £31bn, supporting investments in transport, housing and digital infrastructure</li><li>supporting electric vehicles through £400m charging infrastructure and an extra £100m to extend the plug-in car grant</li><li>boosting our digital infrastructure with over £1bn of public investment, including £176m for 5G and £200m for local areas to encourage roll out of full-fibre networks.</li></ul>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-01-22T16:25:30.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824736/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824736/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824736/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-17","Industry: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the total amount of new spending is to implement the Industrial Strategy.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","123537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824737","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-25","<p>Contracts that my Department holds with Government strategic suppliers are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Count of Contract</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DfT(c)</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DVLA</p></td><td><p>22</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DVSA</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MCA</p></td><td><p>23</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>VCA</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>DfT total </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>96</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-01-25T14:52:57.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824737/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824737/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824737/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-17","Department for Transport: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many contracts his Department holds with government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824738","Department for International Development","false","2018-01-24","<p>The UK Aid Strategy sets out that, “in allocating aid, the government will carefully consider the fit with its strategic objectives, the level of need, the ability of partner countries to finance their own development, and what support they get from others”.</p><p>Where DFID works and DFID’s allocations to different countries are kept under review to ensure UK Aid is used most effectively to achieve poverty reduction in the national interest and responds to changing global needs.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-01-24T17:17:21.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824738/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824738/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824738/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-17","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans she has to introduce new criteria for allocating her Department's overseas aid budget.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","123539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824739","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-25","<p>The Government is committed to maintaining transparency about its procurement activity and publishes information about its contracts with a value of over £10,000 on the “Contracts Finder” website. The information requested is readily available there.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-01-25T14:45:53.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824739/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824739/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824739/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","Treasury: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many contracts his Department holds with Government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824740","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-22","<p>At the Autumn Budget, the government announced it would introduce a transferable tax history for UK exploration and production companies. This is not a tax cut: it is designed to level the playing field between companies established in the sector and new entrants. It will do this by giving those new entrants certainty that tax relief will be available on their decommissioning costs. This measure is consistent with the UK’s existing carbon reduction commitments.</p><p> </p><p>The government is committed to tackling climate change and is a world leader in reducing emissions, having done so faster than any other G7 nation. The latest Energy and Emissions Projections Report shows that the UK remains on track to meet its carbon reduction targets. The Report is available here:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/671187/Updated_energy_and_emissions_projections_2017.pdf</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-01-22T15:53:39.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824740/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824740/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824740/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-17","North Sea Oil: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the tax cuts for North Sea Oil companies in Autumn Budget 2017 on the UK's carbon reduction commitments.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","123541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824741","Home Office","false","2018-01-23","<p>Juxtaposed Controls were introduced for short sea crossings by the “Treaty Between the Government of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland and the Government of the French Republic Concerning the Implementation of Frontier Controls at the Sea ports of Both Countries on the Channel and North Sea”, signed at Le Touquet on 4 February 2003.</p><p>The Le Touquet Treaty is a bilateral agreement and provides for immigration controls to be conducted by the country of arrival in designated control zones in the country of departure at both French and UK sea ports on the Channel and North Sea, including Calais and Dunkirk in France, and Dover in the UK.</p><p>Both countries have in recent discussions reaffirmed their commitment to the agreement and to the continued effective management of our shared border in Northern France.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline  Nokes",,"2018-01-23T16:24:23.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824741/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824741/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824741/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-17","Immigration Controls: France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking under the 2003 Le Touquet accord to ensure that UK border controls are conducted on French soil.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","123542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824742","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-25","<p>The Department of Digital, Culture, Media and Sport holds four such contracts.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-01-25T15:00:07.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824742/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824742/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824742/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-17","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many contracts his Department holds with government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824743","Department for International Development","false","2018-01-24","<p>DFID currently holds 1 centrally managed contract with a Government Strategic Supplier.</p><p>Additionally, DFID pays into a small number of cross-Government corporate contracts with strategic suppliers, from central framework agreements held by the Crown Commercial Service.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-01-24T17:15:18.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824743/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824743/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/824743/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-17","Department for International Development: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many contracts her Department holds with government strategic suppliers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","123544"
